The paper proposes a self-training approach for generative models in molecular design, which involves pre-training the model with a property predictor and iteratively creating additional molecular targets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of neural models and likelihood models for filtering candidate structures suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories.
